The paper proposes a new approach to magnetic resonance imaging using recurrent neural networks, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). The use of neural networks for map reconstruction also suggests a potential connection to information theory (cs.IT).
